le of Aristotelian philosophy in 16th-century knowledge. The volume includes an introductory essay about Cesalpino's philosophy and botany, a critical edition of the Latin text, a translation, a commentary, and indexes. It should interest scholars in Renaissance studies, historians, and philosophers of science and medicine, as well as botanists and plant scientists curious about the history of plant sciences.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aAristotelismus. 4aBotanik. 4aRenaissance. 4aTaxonomie. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh  aRenaissance.  aaristotelism.  aplant sciences.  ataxonomy.1 aTresnie, Corentin, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2023 Englishz978311131908708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2023z9783111318110oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311100016940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311100110440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111001104423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111001104/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  a978-3-11-131908-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_MDPM  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_ECL_MDPM  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV